Design a simple, clean web app UI for a “Robotics Club Budget & Proposal Generator”.

The app should be minimal, professional, and easy to use. It is for students organizing a robotics club to estimate costs and generate a funding proposal.

Limit the design to 2–3 main screens:

1. Input Screen (Main Screen)
- Title: Budget Generator
- Simple form with:
  - Number of teams (input)
  - Budget per team (optional input)
  - Components list (add/remove items with name + cost per item)
- Button: “Calculate Budget”
- Button: “Generate Proposal”

2. Results Screen
- Show:
  - Total estimated cost
  - Cost per team
  - Breakdown of components
- Clean summary cards or sections
- Button: “Edit Inputs”
- Button: “Export / Copy”

3. Proposal Preview Screen (can also be a modal instead of full screen)
- Auto-generated formatted proposal text:
  - short description of the club
  - number of teams
  - requested budget
  - justification
- Button: “Copy Proposal”
- Button: “Download”

Design style:
- Minimal and modern
- Clean spacing, not cluttered
- Card-based layout
- Neutral professional colors (suitable for university use)
- Desktop-first
- Focus on clarity and usability, not fancy visuals
